{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_53","type":"agent_message","text":"The main gap is clearer now. The repo already assembles and stores final audio, but it supersedes prior finals too early and doesn’t expose enough artifact metadata to make regeneration history and current-vs-previous masters obvious. I’m fixing that by:\n- extracting final assembly into a dedicated service\n- keeping prior final audio live until a replacement is successfully published\n- recording first-class runtime and generation metadata on the final asset\n- surfacing enough asset/job linkage for the UI and tests to show when the player is showing a prior master during a new run"}}
