{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_223","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"cd tools/webapp-qa && node --input-type=module <<'EOF'\nimport puppeteer from 'puppeteer';\nconst url = 'http://127.0.0.1:8566/sessions/96474c5c-d84f-4157-8a01-ba97fa241742?stage=audio';\nconst outputPath = '/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-77-audio-stage-diagnostic.png';\nconst browser = await puppeteer.launch({headless: true, args: ['--no-sandbox','--disable-setuid-sandbox']});\ntry {\n  const page = await browser.newPage();\n  page.on('console', (message) => console.log(\"'`[browser:${message.type()}] ${message.text()}`));\n  page.on('\"'pageerror', (error) => console.error(\"'`[browser:pageerror] ${error.message}`));\n  page.on('\"'requestfailed', (request) => console.error(\"'`[browser:requestfailed] ${request.method()} ${request.url()} ${request.failure()?.errorText || '\"''}\"'`));\n  await page.setViewport({ width: 1440, height: 1100 });\n  await page.goto(url, { waitUntil: '\"'domcontentloaded', timeout: 15000 });\n  await new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, 5000));\n  const text = await page.evaluate(() => document.body?.innerText || '');\n  console.log('page:text:begin');\n  console.log(text.slice(0, 4000));\n  console.log('page:text:end');\n  await page.screenshot({ path: outputPath, fullPage: true });\n  console.log(\"'`saved:${outputPath}`);\n} finally {\n  await browser.close();\n}\nEOF'","aggregated_output":"[browser:debug] [vite] connecting...\n[browser:debug] [vite] connected.\n[browser:info] %cDownload the React DevTools for a better development experience: https://react.dev/link/react-devtools font-weight:bold\npage:text:begin\nSkip to main content\n\nBEDTIME STORY STUDIO\n\nStoryteller\nSessions\nWorkspace\n\nResume existing stories or open a session workspace when you are ready to continue.\n\nCONNECTION\n\nBackend reachability\nLast checked 7:07 PM.\nOnline\nCheck again\n\nThe app shell is connected to FastAPI through the Vite development proxy.\n\nHello from FastAPI!\n\nSESSION WORKSPACE\n\nQA Final Audio Assembly\n\nChat and stage-driven workflow controls now share one persistent surface, with the left lane reserved for conversation and the right canvas reserved for structured editing.\n\nCurrent stage\nAudio\nSave status\nSaved Apr 3, 1:59 AM\nSession ID\n96474c5c-d84f-4157-8a01-ba97fa241742\nLive updates\nIdle\n\nSet VITE_SESSION_EVENTS_WS_URL to enable live updates.\n\nNeeds refresh\nReturn home\nLive feed idle\nIn progress\n\nThe workspace is running from the durable snapshot only. Configure the websocket endpoint to start session-scoped live updates.\n\nChat lane\n\nMessages, action echoes, and redirect notes stay visible beside the structured workflow.\n\nLive feed idle\n\nNarration rendering is active. The transcript remains readable while the audio pass runs.\n\nSystem\nApr 3, 1:59 AM\n\nSession opened. Resume at Audio.\n\nMessage composer\n\nSend approvals, nudges, or revision notes without leaving the current workspace stage.\n\nUnavailable\nQuick actions\n\nRun a common action in one tap, or type the slash version.\n\nCommands\nNext stage\nRegenerate pitches\nSummarize plan\n\nSlash commands: /next-stage, /regenerate-pitches, /plan\n\nMessage composer\n\nThe composer is paused while audio generation is active. It will reopen after narration settles.\n\n0/1200 characters\n\nSend message\nWorkflow canvas\n\nThe main pane keeps enough width for forms, stage review, and later composition or audio progress views.\n\nIn progress\nStage navigator\n\nEvery required workflow step is visible now, with URL-backed panel selection that can coexist with backend-owned stage truth.\n\n01\n\nSTAGE 01\n\nGenre\n\nChoose the overall bedtime-story lane before the rest of the plan is shaped.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n02\n\nSTAGE 02\n\nTone\n\nChoose the emotional texture and bedtime-safety posture for the session.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n03\n\nSTAGE 03\n\nStory brief\n\nCapture the user's free-form idea and any normalized planning summary derived from it.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n04\n\nSTAGE 04\n\nPitches\n\nGenerate, compare, refine, and accept candidate story directions.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n05\n\nSTAGE 05\n\nCharacters\n\nDefine the accepted character sheet that later planning and writing will reference.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n06\n\nSTAGE 06\n\nBeat sheet\n\nStore the accepted Save-the-Cat beat sheet for the session.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n07\n\nSTAGE 07\n\nStory setup\n\nStore soft planning targets such as word count, runtime, and chapter structure.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n08\n\nSTAGE 08\n\nComposition\n\nWrite the story durably in segments, with room for interruption and targeted rewrites.\n\nComplete\nRevisitable\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n09\n\nSTAGE 09\n\nAudio\n\nConfigure narration settings and generate resumable audio artifacts.\n\nIn progress\nUnlocked\nThis is the durable current stage saved by the backend.\n10\n\nSTAGE 10\n\nFinalize\n\nRead, listen, review final assets, and download exports.\n\nNeeds refresh\nUnlocked\nAvailable stages can mount richer editors later without changing the shell.\n\nSTAGE SCAFFOLD\n\nConfigure narration and music\n\nThe audio stage will expose narration controls, runtime estimates, and resumable generation progress b\npage:text:end\n[browser:log] [vite] server connection lost. Polling for restart...\