{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_233","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented prompt 77 and left the code in a coherent state on the current branch. The production checkpoint is committed as `cc349e1` (`feat(prompt-77): final audio assembly`), and the required reviewer summary is written to [summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.yolopilot/runs/20260331T205548_storyteller_prompt_pack/77_final_audio_assembly_and_metadata/summary.md).\n\nThe main change is that final narration publishing is now handled by a dedicated backend assembly service with durable metadata and explicit supersession rules. Prior final audio stays available until a replacement publishes successfully, and the session/UI now expose runtime, generation details, download access, and “previous master vs active job” state.\n\nVerification completed:\n- `pytest backend/tests/test_asset_service.py backend/tests/test_story_tools.py -k 'audio or supersede'`\n- `pytest backend/tests/test_session_hydration_service.py backend/tests/test_session_api.py -k 'audio'`\n- `ruff check ...` on the touched backend files\n- `cd frontend && npm test -- --run src/features/session/AudioSettingsStage.test.tsx`\n- `cd frontend && npm run lint -- ...`\n- `cd frontend && npm run build`\n\nBrowser QA was attempted. Docker-based QA was blocked because the Docker daemon was unavailable, and the host-run Puppeteer fallback could render the workspace route but did not produce a reliable screenshot artifact in this environment. The full details, assumptions, and gotchas are in the summary file."}}
